(326, 3, '2019-03-25 18:07:18', '2019-03-25 18:07:18', '<!-- wp:paragraph {\"dropCap\":true} -->\n<p class=\"has-drop-cap\">The Cocora Valley is a beautiful natural landscape located in a mountainous valley of the Central Cordillera of the Colombian Andes in the department of Quindío and is one of the most outstanding tourist destinations in the Coffee Region.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":312} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/cocora-1-Copy-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"valle cocora\" class=\"wp-image-312\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It is distinguished by its fantastic view of green mountains and exuberant vegetation, where the national tree of Colombia \"la Palma de Cera\" is found, which with its imposing height of up to 60 meters, adorns the whole landscape.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":320} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/cocora-2-Copy-293x220.jpg\" alt=\"vlle cocora\" class=\"wp-image-320\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Orejiamarillos parrots live and feed on these trees, as well as other species of animals that are in danger of extinction.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":311} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/cocora-3-Copy-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"valle cocora\" class=\"wp-image-311\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Definitely, the Cocora Valley is mountains, fauna, palm trees, rivers, fog and nature ... Do not miss the opportunity to get to know it! Know your travel options here -&gt;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'The Cocora Valley, an ideal destination for nature lovers.', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-cocora-valley-an-ideal-destination-for-nature-lovers', '', '', '2019-03-25 18:07:48', '2019-03-25 18:07:48', '', 0, 