(338, 3, '2019-03-25 18:20:41', '2019-03-25 18:20:41', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Taste Barranquilla</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>During three days an event is held that highlights the culinary values ​​of the Caribbean and highlights the different currents of the dishes between the indigenous, European and African culture through its maximum exponents. Every year, international, national and local chefs participate in the fair, all of great trajectory, concentrating dozens of exhibitors who show their creations to the world. A festival created in order to highlight the most emblematic dishes of Barranquilla.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A space where chefs of national and international recognition meet to season Barranquilla with recipes, tricks and culinary tips for all palates and visitors have the opportunity to enjoy areas for the exchange of gastronomic knowledge, spaces of delight towards good table and commercial points.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":376} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/imagen-1-Copy-331x220.jpg\" alt=\"colombia\" class=\"wp-image-376\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The fair has a cooking contest for amateurs where a stage is adapted for attendees to enjoy the event, and every year there is a guest country, where the chefs representing the nation prepare the best dishes and traditional flavors of their territory.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":377} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-2-Copy-393x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-377\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In this event you can taste seafood, ceviche fish, patacones, rice with coconut, fried, desserts and fruit juices are part of the dishes, made with local ingredients that are found throughout the year. One of the most visited sections is the desserts, as well as the space where the cocktails are.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":378} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-3-Copy-293x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-378\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A festival with many ingredients and good seasoning that will bring you closer to the culinary culture of the Colombian Caribbean coast.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Feed you</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>El Virrey Park is the location of one of the oldest and most important gastronomy fairs in Colombia, a meeting not only to delight and enjoy the flavors of Colombian cuisine, but to help with social causes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In this event, different activities are carried out for the attendees, such as master classes, live cooking programs, sales of items with great promotions and, additionally, a program of peasant markets is carried out, where the objective is to bring producers and businessmen closer together Colombians with the great restaurants of the country and with the visitors of the event.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":379} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-4-Copy-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-379\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A space to enjoy the gastronomic variety, not only from Colombia, but from different parts of the world, in addition to knowing different cultures because you can enjoy selling crafts, bands and more activities for families</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":380} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-5-Copy-331x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-380\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>During the tour of this gastronomic event there is a compulsory show at the exhibition called \"Knitting Knowledge of the Indigenous People in Bogotá\", where several indigenous artists exhibit their creations that refer to the trees and the strength of the indigenous peoples who have migrated to the Colombian capital.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":381} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-6-Copy-332x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-381\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Bogotá Wine &amp; Food Festival</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This festival is ideal for lovers of wines and good food, this event is joined by the world\'s leading chefs, stars of enology and mixology in Colombia, to offer unique experiences in the restaurants and bars of the capital, In addition, 100% of ticket sales are destined for the execution of social projects that contribute to the construction of a better country.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Here you will be surrounded by expert chefs in gastronomy and wines willing to teach, talk about various topics and make known their exquisite preparations, you will also enjoy lectures, tastings, tastings and many more activities, as well as find a wide variety of national and international wines all types.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":382} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-7-Copy-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-382\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Gastronomic Congress of Popayán</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Popayán is a beautiful Colombian town, an ideal place to take a break and enjoy its landscapes, but above all its food and to honor its culinary culture, every year the National Gastronomy Congress is held every year, an event loaded with academic value that reveals new flavors and proposals.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Every year, Popayán welcomes students, chefs, gastronomy enthusiasts, agricultural producers and companies in the food and beverage sector and who exhibit a range of gastronomic and cultural surprises that make a real party of flavors during all the days of the congress.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":383} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-8-Copy-440x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-383\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you plan to vacation in Colombia during the month of September you can not stop visiting and delighting this conference, where talks, workshops, meetings of different schools of gastronomy are held, besides tasting delicious patillos. You will also spend a very entertaining moment enjoying exhibitions and concerts.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":384} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-9-Copy-329x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-384\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Also, did you know that Popayán is the first city of gastronomy in Colombia within the UNESCO Creative Cities Network? That\'s right, a title that has allowed the region to expand its borders and create commercial, institutional and academic relationships. A delicious experience that you should not miss!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":385} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-10-Copy-314x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-385\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'Gastronomic fairs of Colombia.', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '336-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-03-25 18:20:41', '2019-03-25 18:20:41', '', 336, 'https://new.anditrip.com/336-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(339, 3, '2019-03-25 18:20:41', '2019-03-25 18:20:41', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>品尝巴兰基利亚</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>在为期三天的美食博览会期间，会举办一场活动，突出加勒比海烹饪价值，并且通过其代表性指数，突出目前本土、欧洲、非洲文化菜肴的不同。每年，国内外以及本地的大厨都会参加这个盛会，每一位都有着辉煌的履历，也聚集了一大波想要对全世界展现他们创意的参展商。这是一个为了突出巴兰基利亚最具有代表性的菜肴而设立的节日。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>在这里，国内外认可的厨师们将齐聚巴兰基利亚，为人们奉上各式各样的食谱、技术和烹饪技巧，让他们有机会能享受烹饪知识的交流、舒适餐桌上的欢乐时光以及商业点。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":376} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/imagen-1-Copy-331x220.jpg\" alt=\"colombia\" class=\"wp-image-376\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>博览会还有一个为业余爱好者准备的厨艺比赛，为与会者提供一个舞台让他们欣赏比赛，每年都会有一个国家的大厨代表这个国家准备当地最好的菜肴以及传统风味。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":377} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-2-Copy-393x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-377\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>在博览会上你可以品尝海鲜、酸橘汁腌鱼、油炸香蕉片、椰子米饭、炸物、甜点以及果汁，这都是菜肴的一部分，由全年都能找到的当地食材所做成。人气最旺的地方是甜点，还有鸡尾酒所在的地方。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":378} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-3-Copy-293x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-378\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>这是一个由无数食材和丰富调料组成的节日，它将让你离哥伦比亚加勒比海岸的烹饪文化更进一步。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>一起来品尝美食吧 埃尔维利公园是哥伦比亚最古老以及最重要的美食博览会之一的所在地，它的举办不仅仅为你的味蕾带来快乐与哥伦比亚美食的享受，也是为了帮助社会公益事业。 博览会为参加者举办了丰富的活动，比如大师班、现场烹饪节目、推荐物品售卖等。此外，农民市场项目也在实施，旨在使哥伦比亚生产者和商人与该国的优秀餐厅以及游客更紧密的联系在一起。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":379} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-4-Copy-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-379\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>这里是一个品尝不同美味的地方，它们不仅仅来自哥伦比亚，也来自世界上其他地方，除了去了解不同的文化，你还可以享受工艺品售卖、乐队以及家庭的更多活动的乐趣。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":380} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-5-Copy-331x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-380\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>在这次美食巡展中，博览会上还有一场不得不欣赏的表演，叫作“编织关于波哥大土著居民的知识”。在表演中，几位土著艺术家将展示他们的创作，这些作品是关于树木以及已经移居到哥伦比亚首都的土著居民的力量。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":381} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-6-Copy-332x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-381\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>波哥大红酒&amp;美食节</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>这个节日是红酒与美食爱好者的天堂，很多世界数一数二的大厨明星葡萄酒酿酒家、调酒师将会参加，为波哥大的餐厅和酒吧带来了独特的经历。此外，100%的门票收入被用作社会项目，有助于哥伦比亚建设成为一个更好的国家。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>在这里，你将被美食和葡萄酒的专家所包围，他们很愿意去教授、谈论不同的话题，让大家了解他们精致的准备工作；你还可以聆听讲座、品尝美味和参加其他很多活动，也可以在这里找到国内外所有不同种类的红酒。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":382} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-7-Copy-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-382\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>波帕扬美食大会</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>波帕扬是哥伦比亚一个美丽的小镇，你可以在这里小憩一番，享受美丽的风景，不过最重要的是这里的食物。为了纪念这里的烹饪文化，每年都会举办国家美食大会，这是一个具有学术价值的大会，会上将展示一些新口味和提议的。 每年，波帕扬欢迎学生、厨师、美食爱好者、农业生产者、食品和饮料行业的公司，他们展示了一系列美食和文化惊喜，使这里在大会期间变成了一个真正的口味盛宴。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":383} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-8-Copy-440x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-383\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>如果你打算在9月去哥伦比亚度假，你一定不能错过这个美食大会，在这里，除了品尝美味的食物之外，还见举办各式各样的演讲、研讨会、烹饪学校的会议。你将在这里度过非常快乐的时光，享受这里的展览和音乐会。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":384} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-9-Copy-329x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-384\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>还有，你是到波帕扬是哥伦比亚第一个联合国教科文组织创意城市网络内的美食之城吗？没错，这个头衔得以让这里拓宽边界、建立起商业、制度和学术关系。这将是一趟不容错过的美味体验！</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":385} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-10-Copy-314x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-385\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', '哥伦比亚美食博览会', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '%e5%93%a5%e4%bc%a6%e6%af%94%e4%ba%9a%e7%be%8e%e9%a3%9f%e5%8d%9a%e8%a7%88%e4%bc%9a', '', '', '2019-03-25 18:21:45', '2019-03-25 18:21:45', '', 0, 'http://new.anditrip.com/?p=339', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(340, 3, '2019-03-25 18:21:42', '2019-03-25 18:21:42', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>品尝巴兰基利亚</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>在为期三天的美食博览会期间，会举办一场活动，突出加勒比海烹饪价值，并且通过其代表性指数，突出目前本土、欧洲、非洲文化菜肴的不同。每年，国内外以及本地的大厨都会参加这个盛会，每一位都有着辉煌的履历，也聚集了一大波想要对全世界展现他们创意的参展商。这是一个为了突出巴兰基利亚最具有代表性的菜肴而设立的节日。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>在这里，国内外认可的厨师们将齐聚巴兰基利亚，为人们奉上各式各样的食谱、技术和烹饪技巧，让他们有机会能享受烹饪知识的交流、舒适餐桌上的欢乐时光以及商业点。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":376} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/imagen-1-Copy-331x220.jpg\" alt=\"colombia\" class=\"wp-image-376\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>博览会还有一个为业余爱好者准备的厨艺比赛，为与会者提供一个舞台让他们欣赏比赛，每年都会有一个国家的大厨代表这个国家准备当地最好的菜肴以及传统风味。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":377} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-2-Copy-393x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-377\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>在博览会上你可以品尝海鲜、酸橘汁腌鱼、油炸香蕉片、椰子米饭、炸物、甜点以及果汁，这都是菜肴的一部分，由全年都能找到的当地食材所做成。人气最旺的地方是甜点，还有鸡尾酒所在的地方。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":378} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-3-Copy-293x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-378\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>这是一个由无数食材和丰富调料组成的节日，它将让你离哥伦比亚加勒比海岸的烹饪文化更进一步。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>一起来品尝美食吧 埃尔维利公园是哥伦比亚最古老以及最重要的美食博览会之一的所在地，它的举办不仅仅为你的味蕾带来快乐与哥伦比亚美食的享受，也是为了帮助社会公益事业。 博览会为参加者举办了丰富的活动，比如大师班、现场烹饪节目、推荐物品售卖等。此外，农民市场项目也在实施，旨在使哥伦比亚生产者和商人与该国的优秀餐厅以及游客更紧密的联系在一起。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":379} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-4-Copy-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-379\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>这里是一个品尝不同美味的地方，它们不仅仅来自哥伦比亚，也来自世界上其他地方，除了去了解不同的文化，你还可以享受工艺品售卖、乐队以及家庭的更多活动的乐趣。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":380} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-5-Copy-331x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-380\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>在这次美食巡展中，博览会上还有一场不得不欣赏的表演，叫作“编织关于波哥大土著居民的知识”。在表演中，几位土著艺术家将展示他们的创作，这些作品是关于树木以及已经移居到哥伦比亚首都的土著居民的力量。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":381} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-6-Copy-332x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-381\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>波哥大红酒&amp;美食节</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>这个节日是红酒与美食爱好者的天堂，很多世界数一数二的大厨明星葡萄酒酿酒家、调酒师将会参加，为波哥大的餐厅和酒吧带来了独特的经历。此外，100%的门票收入被用作社会项目，有助于哥伦比亚建设成为一个更好的国家。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>在这里，你将被美食和葡萄酒的专家所包围，他们很愿意去教授、谈论不同的话题，让大家了解他们精致的准备工作；你还可以聆听讲座、品尝美味和参加其他很多活动，也可以在这里找到国内外所有不同种类的红酒。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":382} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-7-Copy-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-382\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>波帕扬美食大会</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>波帕扬是哥伦比亚一个美丽的小镇，你可以在这里小憩一番，享受美丽的风景，不过最重要的是这里的食物。为了纪念这里的烹饪文化，每年都会举办国家美食大会，这是一个具有学术价值的大会，会上将展示一些新口味和提议的。 每年，波帕扬欢迎学生、厨师、美食爱好者、农业生产者、食品和饮料行业的公司，他们展示了一系列美食和文化惊喜，使这里在大会期间变成了一个真正的口味盛宴。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":383} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-8-Copy-440x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-383\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>如果你打算在9月去哥伦比亚度假，你一定不能错过这个美食大会，在这里，除了品尝美味的食物之外，还见举办各式各样的演讲、研讨会、烹饪学校的会议。你将在这里度过非常快乐的时光，享受这里的展览和音乐会。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":384} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-9-Copy-329x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-384\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>还有，你是到波帕扬是哥伦比亚第一个联合国教科文组织创意城市网络内的美食之城吗？没错，这个头衔得以让这里拓宽边界、建立起商业、制度和学术关系。这将是一趟不容错过的美味体验！</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":385} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-10-Copy-314x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-385\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', '哥伦比亚美食博览会', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '339-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-03-25 18:21:42', '2019-03-25 18:21:42', '', 339, 'https://new.anditrip.com/339-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(341, 3, '2019-03-25 18:26:57', '2019-03-25 18:26:57', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Quito, the largest and best preserved historic center.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Quito was the first city in the world to be declared a World Heritage Site by UNESCO. While you walk around its historic center, you step on its cobbled streets, its paved sidewalks you will see churches, houses, colonial convents, built with mud and stone, you will feel like traveling through time through an area rich in history and culture.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The streets of Quito tell their stories and Garcia Moreno Street, also known as Las Siete Cruces, is one of them, besides being one of the most famous. His name is because there are seven crosses on the street. The first cross is outside the San Lorenzo chapel and the second in the Del Carmen Alto monastery, the third is located in the Jesuits\' La Compañía de Jesús Church and is elaborated in the Baroque style and inside it is covered with sheets of gold. The fourth and fifth crosses belong to the El Sagrario church and the Cathedral, and the last two in the La Concepción and Santa Bárbara churches respectively.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":394} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-1-Copy-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-394\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Ronda is another one of the historical, emblematic and famous sectors of the city. Currently there are some restaurants with typical Ecuadorian food, literary and bohemian cafes, in its streets you can see decorative candle manufacturers, sobadores and musicians.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":395} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-2-Copy-1-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-395\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The most extraordinary architectural work in Quito that will be impossible to contemplate is the Church of San Francisco, its structure covers almost two blocks, being the most extensive in the city. In its interior it shelters more than four thousand artistic pieces, among furniture, canvases and sculptures.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":396} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-3-Copy-1-328x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-396\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The white city: Arequipa, Peru.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>They are 330 hectares that occupies the historic center of Arequipia and were declared a World Heritage Site by Unesco. Its religious architecture stands out in this heritage, its white buildings are like jewels that unfold throughout the city and contrast with a beautiful landscape in the background that includes snow-capped volcanoes and the Andes mountain range.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The old town of the so-called white city of Peru contains many stories such as its picturesque San Lazaro neighborhood. A magical area full of squares, small streets, such as the Violin Alley with its particular entrance arch, Cristales Alley, Bayoneta Alley, Naval Combat Alley, among others. The characteristic white color of their buildings is due to the fact that they were built with a volcanic stone known as sillar.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":397} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-4-Copy-1-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-397\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Plaza de Armas is considered one of the most beautiful of the continent, surrounded by three imposing ancient buildings such as: The Cathedral, the Church of the Company and the Church of Our Lady of Mercy. This square captivates both the day with activities and typical restaurants, and at night when its extraordinary monuments are illuminated reaching orange tones, a wonderful spectacle that you have to live and witness.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":398} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-5-Copy-1-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-398\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can not stop contemplating the picturesque and characteristic Arequipia or its beautiful sunsets from the Mirador Yanahuara, one of the most touristic places in the city. This emblematic place is conformed by a succession of sillar arcs and from where in addition to seeing the whole city you can appreciate the imposing and famous Misti volcano, the Chachani and the Pichu Picchu.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":399} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-6-Copy-1-331x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-399\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Transfer to the colonial era in the Casco Viejo of Panama.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The old town of Panama is a World Heritage Site declared by Unesco. This colonial area, located a few minutes from the modern city of Panama, you can explore and feel the magic and grandeur of its history reflected through its architecture, streets and buildings that have been rebuilt and others that have remained in time . In Casco Viejo you can see churches, museums, beautiful squares, theater, the cathedral and each of them have something to tell.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Visit the colonial city and see the vestiges of ancient religious buildings such as the old convent of Santo Domingo, one of the first to be founded in the new city, now you can see the ruins of its facade and internal arches, as well as a chapel that It was totally restored and it serves as a religious museum.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":400} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-7-Copy-1-285x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-400\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You will also like to sit for a while in Plaza Bolívar, one of the most beautiful tourist spots in the city. In the center of the square you will observe the monument to the Venezuelan General Simón Bolívar, known as \"the Liberator of Latin America\". Around the square you can see churches, luxurious hotels, the National Theater and renowned restaurants where you can enjoy excellent traditional and international cuisine.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":401} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-8-Copy-1-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-401\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The National Theater is located diagonally to Plaza Bolívar, a fantastic building that has been restored. Inside, there is a ceiling where there is an impressive mural that exhibits historical figures of Panama, provides a first-rate natural acoustics and has a capacity for 853 people. Here you can enjoy the staging of dance, theater and even musicals.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":402} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-9-Copy-1-332x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-402\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'A trip to the past: colonial cities.', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'a-trip-to-the-past-colonial-cities', '', '', '2019-03-25 18:26:59', '2019-03-25 18:26:59', '', 0, 'http://new.anditrip.com/?p=341', 0, 'post', '', 0),
