y, now you can see the ruins of its facade and internal arches, as well as a chapel that It was totally restored and it serves as a religious museum.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":400} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-7-Copy-1-285x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-400\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You will also like to sit for a while in Plaza Bolívar, one of the most beautiful tourist spots in the city. In the center of the square you will observe the monument to the Venezuelan General Simón Bolívar, known as \"the Liberator of Latin America\". Around the square you can see churches, luxurious hotels, the National Theater and renowned restaurants where you can enjoy excellent traditional and international cuisine.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":401} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-8-Copy-1-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-401\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The National Theater is located diagonally to Plaza Bolívar, a fantastic building that has been restored. Inside, there is a ceiling where there is an impressive mural that exhibits historical figures of Panama, provides a first-rate natural acoustics and has a capacity for 853 people. Here you can enjoy the staging of dance, theater and even musicals.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":402} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-9-Copy-1-332x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-402\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'A trip to the past: colonial cities.', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '341-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-03-25 18:26:57', '2019-03-25 18:26:57', '', 341, 'https://new.anditrip.com/341-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(344, 3, '2019-03-25 18:26:57', '2019-03-25 18:26:57', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>基多，最大且保存最好的历史中心</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>基多是全世界第一座被联合国教科文组织命名为世界文化遗产的城市。当你当你漫步于其历史中心，你的脚步落在它的鹅卵石街道上，在铺设的人行道上，你可以看到很多用泥和石头建造而成的教堂、房屋和殖民修道院，你会感觉就像进行了一场时空旅行，来到了一个充满丰富历史和文化的地方。 基多的街道诉说着它们的故事。加西亚莫雷诺街，也叫作七个十字架，是众多街道其中的一条，也是其中最有名的街道之一。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>它的名字由来是因为在街上有七个十字架。第一个十字架在圣洛伦佐教堂外，第二个在卡门修道院里，第三个位于耶稣会的拉孔尼亚德耶稣教堂，以巴洛克风格精心设计，内部以金箔覆盖，第四和第五个十字架属于El Sagrario教堂和大教堂，最后两个分别在La Concepción和Santa Bárbara教堂。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":394} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-1-Copy-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-394\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ronda是基多另一个最有名且最具有历史意义和象征性的地区。这里如今又很多典型厄瓜多尔风味的餐厅、文学以及波西米亚咖啡馆，在这里的街道上你可以看到精心打扮的蜡烛制造商和音乐家。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":395} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-2-Copy-1-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-395\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>基多最杰出的建筑作品是圣弗朗西斯科教堂，它的结构覆盖了两个街区，是城市里最宽广的。在其内部，有超过四千件艺术作品，包括家具、画布和雕像。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":396} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-3-Copy-1-328x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-396\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>白色之城：秘鲁——阿雷基帕</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>阿雷基帕拥有一个占地330公顷的历史中心，被联合国教科文组织命名为世界文化遗址。它的宗教建筑在这片文化遗产中脱颖而出，它的白色楼房就像珠宝展露在城市中，与山顶被白雪覆盖的火山和安第斯山脉这美丽的背景形成了鲜明对比。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>被称为白色之城的秘鲁老城蕴藏着许多故事，比如它风景如画的San Lazaro街区。这是一个神奇的地方，布满了又方又小的街道，比如有着特殊如楼拱门的小提琴巷、Cristales巷、 Bayoneta巷、海军战斗巷等。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>白色的建筑特征是因为它们是由一种叫sillar的火山石建造而成。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":397} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-4-Copy-1-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-397\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>武器广场被认为是世界上最美的广场之一，周围被三幢古老壮观的建筑围绕：大教堂、公司教堂以及圣母玛利亚教堂。这个广场日夜吸引着游客，白天有丰富的活动和经典餐厅，在夜晚，杰出的纪念碑被照亮，达到橙色的色调，这将是一个你不得不去体验与见证的无与伦比且壮观的景象。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":398} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-5-Copy-1-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-398\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>你情不自禁的注视着风景如画与极具特色的阿雷基帕，或是它Yanahuara眺望台的美丽日落，这也是全城最吸引游客的地方之一。这个具有象征性的地方由一连串的扁圆形弧形构成，从这个可以眺望全城的地方，你可以欣赏著名壮观的米斯蒂火山米斯蒂火山、查查尼峰还有马丘比丘。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":399} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-6-Copy-1-331x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-399\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>穿越回殖民时代 ——巴拿马Casco Viejo老城区</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>巴拿马的老城被联合国教科文组织命名为世界文化遗产。这个殖民地区位于距离巴拿马新城几分钟的距离，你可以通过这里的建筑、街道和楼房探索和感受它历史的魔力与伟大，有些被重新翻新过，剩余的还保留着那个时代的样子。在 Casco Viejo老城区，你可以看到教堂、博物馆、美丽的广场、剧院、大教堂，每一处都蕴藏着着他们自己的故事。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>游览殖民城市，品味古老宗教建筑留下的痕迹，比如老圣多明哥修道院，新城里第一个被发现的宗教建筑，如今你可以看到外观的废墟和内部的拱门，还有它旁边的小教堂，如今成为了一个宗教博物馆。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":400} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-7-Copy-1-285x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-400\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>你还会喜欢在Bolívar广场小憩一番，这座城市最美的景点之一。在广场的中心你可以看到委内瑞拉将军Simón Bolívar的纪念碑，他被誉为“拉丁美洲的解放者”。在广场周围你可以看到很多教堂、奢华酒店、国家剧院和著名的饭店。在这里，你可以先手美妙的传统与国际美食。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":401} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-8-Copy-1-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-401\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>国家剧院位于Bolívar广场斜对角，是一座被修复过的迷人建筑。天花板上有令人震惊的壁画，展示了巴拿马的历史形象，提供一流的自然音响，可容纳853人。在这里你可以欣赏舞蹈、话剧以及音乐剧。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":402} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-9-Copy-1-332x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-402\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', '通往过去的旅行：殖名城市', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '%e9%80%9a%e5%be%80%e8%bf%87%e5%8e%bb%e7%9a%84%e6%97%85%e8%a1%8c%ef%bc%9a%e6%ae%96%e5%90%8d%e5%9f%8e%e5%b8%82', '', '', '2019-03-25 18:27:45', '2019-03-25 18:27:45', '', 0, 'http://new.anditrip.com/?p=344', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(345, 3, '2019-03-25 18:27:42', '2019-03-25 18:27:42', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>基多，最大且保存最好的历史中心</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>基多是全世界第一座被联合国教科文组织命名为世界文化遗产的城市。当你当你漫步于其历史中心，你的脚步落在它的鹅卵石街道上，在铺设的人行道上，你可以看到很多用泥和石头建造而成的教堂、房屋和殖民修道院，你会感觉就像进行了一场时空旅行，来到了一个充满丰富历史和文化的地方。 基多的街道诉说着它们的故事。加西亚莫雷诺街，也叫作七个十字架，是众多街道其中的一条，也是其中最有名的街道之一。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>它的名字由来是因为在街上有七个十字架。第一个十字架在圣洛伦佐教堂外，第二个在卡门修道院里，第三个位于耶稣会的拉孔尼亚德耶稣教堂，以巴洛克风格精心设计，内部以金箔覆盖，第四和第五个十字架属于El Sagrario教堂和大教堂，最后两个分别在La Concepción和Santa Bárbara教堂。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":394} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-1-Copy-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-394\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ronda是基多另一个最有名且最具有历史意义和象征性的地区。这里如今又很多典型厄瓜多尔风味的餐厅、文学以及波西米亚咖啡馆，在这里的街道上你可以看到精心打扮的蜡烛制造商和音乐家。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":395} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-2-Copy-1-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-395\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>基多最杰出的建筑作品是圣弗朗西斯科教堂，它的结构覆盖了两个街区，是城市里最宽广的。在其内部，有超过四千件艺术作品，包括家具、画布和雕像。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":396} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-3-Copy-1-328x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-396\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>白色之城：秘鲁——阿雷基帕</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>阿雷基帕拥有一个占地330公顷的历史中心，被联合国教科文组织命名为世界文化遗址。它的宗教建筑在这片文化遗产中脱颖而出，它的白色楼房就像珠宝展露在城市中，与山顶被白雪覆盖的火山和安第斯山脉这美丽的背景形成了鲜明对比。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>被称为白色之城的秘鲁老城蕴藏着许多故事，比如它风景如画的San Lazaro街区。这是一个神奇的地方，布满了又方又小的街道，比如有着特殊如楼拱门的小提琴巷、Cristales巷、 Bayoneta巷、海军战斗巷等。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>白色的建筑特征是因为它们是由一种叫sillar的火山石建造而成。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":397} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-4-Copy-1-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-397\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>武器广场被认为是世界上最美的广场之一，周围被三幢古老壮观的建筑围绕：大教堂、公司教堂以及圣母玛利亚教堂。这个广场日夜吸引着游客，白天有丰富的活动和经典餐厅，在夜晚，杰出的纪念碑被照亮，达到橙色的色调，这将是一个你不得不去体验与见证的无与伦比且壮观的景象。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":398} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-5-Copy-1-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-398\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>你情不自禁的注视着风景如画与极具特色的阿雷基帕，或是它Yanahuara眺望台的美丽日落，这也是全城最吸引游客的地方之一。这个具有象征性的地方由一连串的扁圆形弧形构成，从这个可以眺望全城的地方，你可以欣赏著名壮观的米斯蒂火山米斯蒂火山、查查尼峰还有马丘比丘。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":399} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-6-Copy-1-331x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-399\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>穿越回殖民时代 ——巴拿马Casco Viejo老城区</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>巴拿马的老城被联合国教科文组织命名为世界文化遗产。这个殖民地区位于距离巴拿马新城几分钟的距离，你可以通过这里的建筑、街道和楼房探索和感受它历史的魔力与伟大，有些被重新翻新过，剩余的还保留着那个时代的样子。在 Casco Viejo老城区，你可以看到教堂、博物馆、美丽的广场、剧院、大教堂，每一处都蕴藏着着他们自己的故事。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>游览殖民城市，品味古老宗教建筑留下的痕迹，比如老圣多明哥修道院，新城里第一个被发现的宗教建筑，如今你可以看到外观的废墟和内部的拱门，还有它旁边的小教堂，如今成为了一个宗教博物馆。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":400} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-7-Copy-1-285x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-400\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>你还会喜欢在Bolívar广场小憩一番，这座城市最美的景点之一。在广场的中心你可以看到委内瑞拉将军Simón Bolívar的纪念碑，他被誉为“拉丁美洲的解放者”。在广场周围你可以看到很多教堂、奢华酒店、国家剧院和著名的饭店。在这里，你可以先手美妙的传统与国际美食。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":401} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-8-Copy-1-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-401\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>国家剧院位于Bolívar广场斜对角，是一座被修复过的迷人建筑。天花板上有令人震惊的壁画，展示了巴拿马的历史形象，提供一流的自然音响，可容纳853人。在这里你可以欣赏舞蹈、话剧以及音乐剧。</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":402} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Imagen-9-Copy-1-332x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-402\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', '通往过去的旅行：殖名城市', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '344-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-03-25 18:27:42', '2019-03-25 18:27:42', '', 344, 'https://new.anditrip.com/344-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(346, 3, '2019-03-25 18:32:34', '2019-03-25 18:32:34', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The most beautiful corners of Buenos Aires, Argentina</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Known as \"the Paris of South America\" ​​the capital of Argentina keeps a myriad of charms that make it unique, as you walk through its streets you will observe its architecture that will transport you to a colonial era, where the deco and neoclassical art that coexist to show the perfect combination between traditional and contemporary. Their culture is felt and felt in every corner, this incredible city offers unforgettable experiences that are entertaining, very enriching and that you can not stop enjoying if you plan to travel to this wonderful metropolis.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>La Boca neighborhood: one of the most visited by tourists, walking during the day is the most recommended to appreciate their brightly colored houses that were built by Italian immigrants with materials left over from the maritime trade and that will undoubtedly leave you captivated . In this area there is a very famous street known as Caminito, its name comes from a famous tango song composed by Gabino Coria Peñaloza and that bears that name, the area is an open-air museum of great cultural and tourist value where you can observe couples dancing tango on its cobblestone streets, an artisan market where paintings, souvenirs, handicrafts and paintings are sold.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":475} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Imagen-1-Copy-357x220.jpg\" alt=\"aregentina\" class=\"wp-image-475\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>La Recoleta: full of elegance and romance, concentrates important buildings of the city of remarkable beauty with a French style, has large parks of beautiful greenery, museums and several places to entertain. As areas of interest are the Recoleta cemetery, the Church of Our Lady of Pilar and the Grand Splendid theater, in the latter is currently the El Ateneo Bookshop and is an icon of the area, its spaces are extraordinary and impressive, a place that is worth visiting so do not go buy books or read, because where once were the seats and balconies are now hundreds of books, and its stage works like a cafeteria.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":476} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Imagen-2-Copy-337x220.jpg\" alt=\"la recoleta argentina\" class=\"wp-image-476\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Palermo: is the most extensive and cosmopolitan neighborhood of the City of Buenos Aires, one of its charms is the architecture of its houses that still conserve the massive original openings, with high ceilings and with a central patio. The beautiful Avenues of Palermo, its green landscape full of trees and elegant homes make this place an ideal destination for tourists, in addition this picturesque barium is full of thematic bars, restaurants, art galleries, design houses that are worth visiting and discover.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":477} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Imagen-3-Copy-331x220.jpg\" alt=\"palermo argentina\" class=\"wp-image-477\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The picturesque Valparaiso, Chile</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Its historical case is a World Heritage Site and is one of the most picturesque cities in Chile, the architecture of their homes, deployed in the hills near the bay, exhibit a mixture of eccentricities, ancient wealth and colorful walls that together with street art It gives an air of modernity to this characteristic place. Its historic buildings house hotels, shops, famous restaurants and museums, without a doubt, Valparaiso is a colorful landscape facing the sea that is worth enjoying!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Discover the stories that hide the stairs, lifts and picturesque homes of the Cerros Alegre and Concepcion, typical areas of the city and where you will live experiences that will leave memorable memories. Going through its small streets and stairs is getting lost in beautiful murals and a beautiful landscape that gives you the ocean, its cafes and bohemian style that characterize these emblematic scenarios.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":478} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Imagen-4-Copy-391x220.jpg\" alt=\"valparaiso chile\" class=\"wp-image-478\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To visit these hills you can make use of the funicular, vehicles that are used to communicate the low areas of the city, in Valparaiso there are 16 elevators and the so-called El Peral is the one that connects Alegre and Concepción hills. Many of them still maintain their original appearance and stand out for being picturesque wooden wagons of different colors on rails, which combine with the facades of their emblematic houses.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":479} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Imagen-5-Copy-293x220.jpg\" alt=\"el peral chile\" class=\"wp-image-479\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To delve into the culture of Valparaiso you can visit La Sebastiana, a museum house belonging to the poet Pablo Neruda. By doing the tour you can enjoy a visit to the past and discover on each floor the life and the most glorious moments who was its owner. You also have the opportunity to review the work of the poet in different languages ​​his life through an exhibition of biographical photographs.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":480} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Imagen-6-Copy-332x220.jpg\" alt=\"la sebastiana chile\" class=\"wp-image-480\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Live the experience in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Considered one of the most beautiful cities in South America and that will leave you breathless, colorful, full of life and you can contemplate its spectacular views and its sinuous mountains, as well as enjoy its famous beaches and carnivals. It is a fascinating and diverse destination, the home of cariocas, an iconic culture and one of the most touristic places in Brazil. Get ready, explore and feel the most of this experience in Rio!<br>The most emblematic place that you find in Rio de Janeiro is 709 meters above sea level, it is impressive and welcomes you with open arms, it is known as the Christ the Redeemer and it is a statue that measures 30 meters high, a viewpoint where You will enjoy a wonderful landscape of the city in 360 degree vision, to get there you can use a funicular.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":481} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Imagen-7-Copy-352x220.jpg\" alt=\"rio de janeiro brasil\" class=\"wp-image-481\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>From any part of the city you can see a suggestive rock, known as \"Pan de Azucar\", another of the stops you must make in Rio de Janeiro. Although its name is due to the shape of a clay mold that was used to refine sugar this site is a green paradise, it is surrounded by nature and is ideal for taking photos, you can also enjoy a breathtaking view of everything River.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":482} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Imagen-8-Copy-355x220.jpg\" alt=\"pan de azucar brasil\" class=\"wp-image-482\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Rio de Janeiro is famous for its beaches, but there is an exclusive neighborhood that is full of trendy shops and luxury restaurants, it is called Ipanema, here you will also enjoy art galleries and craft markets. You can visit the National Historical Museum that houses one of the most incredible collections of art, documents, weapons and pieces related to the history of Brazil.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":483} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Imagen-9-Copy-391x220.jpg\" alt=\"ipanema brazil\" class=\"wp-image-483\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'The most beautiful cities in Latin America', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-most-beautiful-cities-in-latin-america', '', '', '2019-03-25 18:32:41', '2019-03-25 18:32:41', '', 0, 'http://new.anditrip.com/?p=346', 0, 'post', '', 0),
