(361, 3, '2019-03-25 18:44:41', '2019-03-25 18:44:41', '<!-- wp:paragraph {\"dropCap\":true} -->\n<p class=\"has-drop-cap\">It is the largest tropical forest in the world that surrounds the Amazon River basin, an area of ​​5,500,000 km2 that is shared by Brazil, Peru, Colombia, Bolivia, Ecuador, Guyana, Venezuela and Suriname, both being the first where most of the territory is located. The Amazon is full of charms, exotic species, captivating landscapes and adventures that you must live when you plan to visit South America.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Amazon has an incomparable biodiversity and one of the richest in the world, has forests with incredible trees, so high that you will lose sight of them, also houses some 3000 species of fruits and all are edible, in addition there are many species of medicinal plants and variety of wild flowers that captivate you with their unique beauty and colorful</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":498} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Imagen-1-Copy-3-321x220.jpg\" alt=\"amazon\" class=\"wp-image-498\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Its fauna is amazing and varied, which includes 2500 types of fish, like the gray and pink dolphins of the Amazon, it is also the home of piranhas. In this jungle you will observe thousands of species of birds that adorn the landscape with their colorful plumage, millions of insects, hundreds of mammals, such as the titi monkey, small sized animals with a soft and silky coat, currently the majority of the species are considered threat as a result of the destruction of their habitat.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":499} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Imagen-2-Copy-3-331x220.jpg\" alt=\"amazon\" class=\"wp-image-499\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Amazon is not only the largest forest on the planet, it is also the ancestral home of indigenous groups. In it there are a variety of natives, with an approximate of 350 ethnic groups scattered in different tribes, each with its own language and culture. Some of them have never had contact with civilization.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":500} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Imagen-3-Copy-3-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"amazon\" class=\"wp-image-500\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the Amazon you can enjoy excursions and go into the jungle to know and visit and visit the different populations of the natives, their culture and traditions, in this green paradise you can admire exuberant landscapes and explore part of the Amazon River. An ideal plan for lovers of ecotourism and adventure sports.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":502} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Imagen-4-Copy-2-331x220.jpg\" alt=\"amazon\" class=\"wp-image-502\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'The Amazon and its charms', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-amazon-and-its-charms', '', '', '2019-03-25 18:44:44', '2019-03-25 18:44:44', '', 0, 'http://new.anditrip.com/?p=361', 0, 'post', '', 0),
