image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>伊卡，秘鲁的历史和红酒。<br>伊卡是秘鲁皮斯科酒的发源地，是秘鲁一种典型的饮料。<br>伊卡是秘鲁沿海沙漠和安第斯山脉的一部分，是全国农业出口潜力最大的中心之一，因此赋予了它重要的社会经济地位。然而事实上，这里是葡萄酒庄园最早起源的地方，由西班牙人带来，一段时间后，传播到智利和阿根廷。在这里你可以游览不同的庄园和葡萄酒园，在这里你可以目睹皮斯科酒和这个地区红酒从生产过程到产品的过程。<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":588} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-6-Copy-383x220.jpeg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-588\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>秘鲁这个区域另一个吸引人的地方是帕拉卡斯国家自然保护区，一个海洋和沙漠被保护的部分，为了保护这里当地不同的物种和迁徙的鸟儿，例如鹈鹕、企鹅、火烈鸟，还有其他哺乳动物。这里的岛屿、沙漠、悬崖和沙滩占地有335公顷，由于其令人印象深刻的自然美景，每年吸引着当地和海外的游客前来。<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":589} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-7-Copy-293x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-589\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>谈及秘鲁，不只有印加文化，还有纳斯卡文化，你可以在安东尼奥博物馆和玛利亚瑞奇博物馆里了解到更多，这里曾经是一个德国女人的家，她曾致力于研究纳斯卡曲线，并被联合国教科文组织命名为人类世界文化遗产。在安东尼奥博物馆，你可以看到纳斯卡文化不同时期的考古样本，例如织物等。另外，你还可以欣赏Bisambra隧道，其展示了纳斯卡文化这个时期伟大的水力工程。<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":590} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-8-Copy-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-590\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>门多萨，阿根廷最重要的红酒中心<br>以国际红酒之都而闻名，在门多萨，你可以欣赏自然、文化活动和最好的美食。它的自然特征为生产不同类型的优质葡萄酒提供了理想的条件，其中马尔贝克葡萄酒最为突出，其酒香在其他地区很难找到。<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":591} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-9-Copy-455x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-591\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>全年被树木与适宜的气候所包围，这座阿根廷城市的山脉是其主角，毫无疑问是你想前往的地方。<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":592} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-10-Copy-367x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-592\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>在市区你可以找到不同的博物馆和艺术画廊，其中有葡萄酒博物馆，Cuyano 的过往博物馆以及基础地区博物馆，包含了一个藏有门多萨地房间与门多萨的卡比尔多考古遗迹。参观他们将让你了解和了解门多萨的文化，以及品尝该地区生产的葡萄酒的精美样品。<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":586} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-11-Copy-391x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-586\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>这里还有令人满意的户外活动。在门多萨，你可以享受温泉水，辅以酒店和水疗设施。同时，在门多萨河，几乎全年都可以进行漂流，如果我们稍微再远离城市一点，就可以到达firewoods，一个垂直不均匀度为1200米的滑雪中心，有住宿和美食一流棒。<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', '精致之旅。南美红酒品尝。', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '399-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-03-25 19:44:23', '2019-03-25 19:44:23', '', 399, 'https://new.anditrip.com/399-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(401, 3, '2019-03-25 19:49:59', '2019-03-25 19:49:59', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Brazil and Argentina share a wonder.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":602} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-1-Copy-3-332x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-602\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Formed by the Iguazú River that originates in the state of Paraná, Brazil, the falls of the same name are found within the Iguazú National Park, some 20 kilometers from the city of Puerto Iguazú, north of the province of Misiones, Argentina.<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":599} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-2-Copy-3-293x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-599\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Declared natural heritage of humanity in 1984, in 2011 they were nominated for an international contest as one of the 7 Natural Wonders of the World, shared by two beautiful countries.<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":600} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-3-Copy-3-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-600\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The energy they transmit is incredible. It treats falls of water of up to 80 meters, in the middle of a dense forest to which it is possible to accede by different means. In the place, there are walkways and viewpoints from which it is possible to contemplate its majesty and enjoy this spectacle of nature.<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":601} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Imagen-4-Copy-3-293x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-601\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>However, you can be more than a spectator. It is possible to take guided tours through the adjacent jungle and admire the great diversity of flora and fauna present in the place. You can get to the Iguazú Falls on the Argentine side or on the Brazilian side, and the cities of both countries have hotels and tourist services so you can get to know this wonder, with all the amenities you want.<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Iguazu falls', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'iguazu-falls', '', '', '2019-03-25 19:50:02', '2019-03-25 19:50:02', '', 0, 'http://new.anditrip.com/?p=401', 0, 'post', '', 0),
