(416, 3, '2019-03-25 20:10:16', '2019-03-25 20:10:16', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Andes mountain range crosses the continent and gives us incredible landscapes that you can not miss.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Los Glaciares Park, Argentina.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Its main attraction is the Perito Moreno Glacier, which in 2016 alone received 693,584 tourists. In 1981 it was declared a World Heritage Site by UNESCO and is one of the most impressive landscapes you can find in the south of the continent. Its majestic masses of ice and the mountains around it, constitute an imposing almost fantastic scenario, which both tourists and locals can not help but admire.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":629} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/1.parque-los-glaciares-Copy-330x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-629\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On the other hand, Mount Fitz Roy with 3,376 m, is one of the most impressive landscapes you can find and walk, and that along with the area of ​​El Chaltén, with all the charm that being a small town at the foot of the mountain confers, it is one of the tourist treasures that Patagonia has for you.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":626} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/2.parque-los-glaciares-Copy-329x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-626\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Torres del Paine National Park, Chile<br>Lakes of blue waters, beautiful forests with a great diversity of flora and fauna, make this national park one of the richest in the continent. Its main summit reaches 3050 meters above sea level, in 1978 it was declared a Biosphere Reserve by UNESCO, and the diversity of its relief and variety of resources make it one of the best destinations for ecotourism and adventure sports and mountain, reason why in 2013 TripAdvisor Media Group called it the eighth wonder of the world.<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":627} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/3.parque-torres-del-paine-Copy-293x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-627\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The best thing is that very close you can find beautiful luxury hotels with all the comforts you can access in the city, but with the charm that these wonderful natural spaces have to offer.<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":628} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/4.parque-torres-del-paine2-Copy-294x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-628\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Alpamayo, Peru.<br>In the white mountain range of the Peruvian Andes is this peak that in 1966 was described as \'the most beautiful mountain in the world\', in a scenic photography contest held that year in Germany. Located at 5.947 meters above sea level, it is possible to take a walk around it where you will admire all the flora and fauna of the Andean highlands that are grouped in the place. The lagoons and glaciers are not lacking, and give it that mystical air that, together with its picturesque native villages, make it a special destination not only for its natural characteristics, but also for its cultural richness.<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":625} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://anditrip.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/5.alpamayo2-Copy-293x220.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-625\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'The charm of snow. Know the coldest places in South America.', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-charm-of-snow-know-the-coldest-places-in-south-america', '', '', '2019-03-25 20:10:19', '2019-03-25 20:10:19', '', 0, 'http://new.anditrip.com/?p=416', 0, 'post', '', 0),
